WEBVTT

1
00:00:05.527 --> 00:00:07.945
[Alvez] <i>Previously on</i>
Criminal Minds: Evolution...

2
00:00:07.946 --> 00:00:11.198
I used your birth name
and you didn't even notice.

3
00:00:11.199 --> 00:00:16.620
This is where Lee Duval died
and where Elias Voit was born.

4
00:00:16.621 --> 00:00:20.667
Do you feel in your heart of hearts
that you're a good person?

5
00:00:21.167 --> 00:00:24.254
I feel like I can be.

6
00:00:26.047 --> 00:00:28.674
I wouldn't trouble you were it
not of the utmost importance.

7
00:00:28.675 --> 00:00:30.467
[Prentiss on phone]
<i>What is it you think you have?</i>

8
00:00:30.468 --> 00:00:32.427
[Brian]
Dare I say a manifesto.

9
00:00:32.428 --> 00:00:36.349
"Some may call me a fan.
but He must call me God."

10
00:00:37.517 --> 00:00:39.810
- [Voit] Hello. Brian.
- Whoa. Special guest appearance?

11
00:00:39.811 --> 00:00:42.688
Do not say one word about him being here.

12
00:00:42.689 --> 00:00:44.690
Hi. you're live on the air.

13
00:00:44.691 --> 00:00:46.567
With whom
do we have the pleasure of speaking?

14
00:00:46.568 --> 00:00:47.819
[Lance] <i>Call me God.</i>

15
00:00:51.531 --> 00:00:53.031
"Are you trying to profile me?"

16
00:00:53.032 --> 00:00:55.118
I'm not speaking to you.

17
00:00:55.618 --> 00:01:00.497
I'm speaking to Lance Kingston.
the man you're holding captive.

18
00:01:00.498 --> 00:01:01.873
Penelope. talk to me.

19
00:01:01.874 --> 00:01:03.333
Okay. I got him. I got him.

20
00:01:03.334 --> 00:01:06.795
He's at the Stash-All Storage Facility
in Richmond. Virginia.

21
00:01:06.796 --> 00:01:09.256
It's a garage unit being
rented by Lance Kingston.

22
00:01:09.257 --> 00:01:11.675
- [Lance] <i>Is he there?</i>
- Is who here?

23
00:01:11.676 --> 00:01:13.468
- [Lance] <i>Voit.</i>
- No.

24
00:01:13.469 --> 00:01:15.929
[screams]

25
00:01:15.930 --> 00:01:17.639
<i>Stop! He's gonna kill me.</i>

26
00:01:17.640 --> 00:01:19.641
- Yes. he's here.
- No!

27
00:01:19.642 --> 00:01:21.226
- Voit is here! Elias Voit is here.
- [Lance screams]

28
00:01:21.227 --> 00:01:22.228
You can talk to him.

29
00:01:24.063 --> 00:01:25.440
What just happened?

30
00:01:26.482 --> 00:01:28.067
You just caused a man's death.

31
00:01:43.875 --> 00:01:46.376
We've got roadblocks up
in a five and ten mile radius.

32
00:01:46.377 --> 00:01:48.754
We might have a victim inside.
and he might still be alive.

33
00:01:48.755 --> 00:01:50.298
FBI. open up!

34
00:02:03.186 --> 00:02:04.603
Oh. Jesus.

35
00:02:04.604 --> 00:02:06.313
Is that...

36
00:02:06.314 --> 00:02:07.523
It's flesh.

37
00:02:08.149 --> 00:02:09.734
- Burnt flesh.
- [Lewis grunts]

38
00:02:25.500 --> 00:02:27.167
[Lewis] He's been branded.

39
00:02:27.168 --> 00:02:28.169
[grunts]

40
00:02:30.838 --> 00:02:34.216
The residual smoke from the burn
would only last five to ten minutes.

41
00:02:34.217 --> 00:02:36.385
Well. then the Fan
couldn't have gotten far.

42
00:02:36.386 --> 00:02:37.804
[inhales] Let's go.

43
00:02:42.266 --> 00:02:44.102
- You find a pulse?
- It's there.

44
00:02:45.228 --> 00:02:47.187
It's weak and thready. but it's there.

45
00:02:47.188 --> 00:02:50.900
[screaming. sobbing]

46
00:02:52.568 --> 00:02:54.779
[♪ theme music playing]

47
00:03:01.994 --> 00:03:05.288
[Lewis] <i>Do not seek to follow
in the footsteps of the wise.</i>

48
00:03:05.289 --> 00:03:07.082
<i>Seek what they sought.</i>

49
00:03:07.083 --> 00:03:08.583
<i>Matsuo Bashō.</i>

50
00:03:08.584 --> 00:03:10.920
[breathes heavily]

51
00:03:12.964 --> 00:03:15.425
[inhales. exhales]

52
00:03:16.426 --> 00:03:19.928
[exhales] Lance Kingston is alive.

53
00:03:19.929 --> 00:03:20.930
Oh!

54
00:03:21.639 --> 00:03:22.807
Thank God!

55
00:03:23.725 --> 00:03:24.891
Oh!

56
00:03:24.892 --> 00:03:27.895
Oh... [panting] ...Oh!

57
00:03:28.563 --> 00:03:30.480
Sheila said this.

58
00:03:30.481 --> 00:03:32.983
She said this... [inhales]
...right before she left me.

59
00:03:32.984 --> 00:03:35.360
She said. "You're going to get
somebody hurt." [sniffles]

60
00:03:35.361 --> 00:03:37.112
And then it came true. She was right.

61
00:03:37.113 --> 00:03:41.408
I don't know how it happened.
but she was right. Ah! [screams]

62
00:03:41.409 --> 00:03:42.910
Pfft. [exhales]

63
00:03:50.668 --> 00:03:52.295
I am done.

64
00:03:53.379 --> 00:03:56.840
No more <i>Sicarius Files</i>.
No more conspiracies.

65
00:03:56.841 --> 00:03:59.009
I am out for real.

66
00:03:59.010 --> 00:04:01.303
- For real?
- Absolutely!

67
00:04:01.304 --> 00:04:04.556
What happened to Lance is gonna weigh
on my heart for the rest of my life.

68
00:04:04.557 --> 00:04:07.768
Oh. I'm sorry to say this.
but I'm very happy to hear that.

69
00:04:08.394 --> 00:04:12.147
I'm kinda over-leveraged right now
because of the success of the podcast.

70
00:04:12.148 --> 00:04:15.192
I was okay before the money or the perks.

71
00:04:15.193 --> 00:04:18.028
I mean. I'll... [stutters] ...find a way
to be fine again.

72
00:04:18.029 --> 00:04:19.112
Yeah.

73
00:04:19.113 --> 00:04:20.114
[sighs]

74
00:04:23.576 --> 00:04:25.453
[both sigh]

75
00:04:26.370 --> 00:04:28.622
[chuckles. grunts]

76
00:04:28.623 --> 00:04:29.624
Wait.

77
00:04:30.917 --> 00:04:32.626
did you throw up in here?

78
00:04:32.627 --> 00:04:35.545
I was literally sick with worry.

79
00:04:35.546 --> 00:04:39.007
- Emily. I'm so sorry.
- [grunts]

80
00:04:39.008 --> 00:04:40.343
Bill me for a new one.

81
00:04:41.177 --> 00:04:42.678
like a fancy one.

82
00:04:43.638 --> 00:04:44.763
[Prentiss] Ugh.

83
00:04:44.764 --> 00:04:48.350
Is Brian Garrity moonlighting
as a janitor for the FBI?

84
00:04:48.351 --> 00:04:49.643
[sighs] No.

85
00:04:49.644 --> 00:04:52.646
He is not moonlighting
as anything anymore.

86
00:04:52.647 --> 00:04:54.524
Good. because we just got this.

87
00:04:56.567 --> 00:04:57.777
Mm-hmm.

88
00:04:59.111 --> 00:05:00.446
[Prentiss exhales]

89
00:05:08.204 --> 00:05:09.412
Look at this.

90
00:05:09.413 --> 00:05:10.705
What's this?

91
00:05:10.706 --> 00:05:13.793
Crime scene report from the storage locker
where we found Lance.

92
00:05:15.086 --> 00:05:18.296
Well. it's pristine.
Is this post-forensics?

93
00:05:18.297 --> 00:05:20.090
This is the forensics.

94
00:05:20.091 --> 00:05:23.176
No fibers. no hair. no nothing.

95
00:05:23.177 --> 00:05:26.763
And based on the Fan's OCD.
I doubt he left any trace.

96
00:05:26.764 --> 00:05:29.057
Which means you probably struck out too.
didn't you?

97
00:05:29.058 --> 00:05:30.935
Yeah. I did.

98
00:05:31.561 --> 00:05:35.438
The Fan paid for the storage
unit in cash under Lance's name.

99
00:05:35.439 --> 00:05:40.569
and the rental agreement was typed up
on the same typewriter we know so well.

100
00:05:40.570 --> 00:05:44.699
Which he also used
when he escalated to this.

101
00:05:45.241 --> 00:05:47.742
There are eight
letters in the word pathetic.

102
00:05:47.743 --> 00:05:51.496
so the Fan put eight brands
on each of Lance's arms.

103
00:05:51.497 --> 00:05:52.873
Oh.

104
00:05:52.874 --> 00:05:53.958
What?

105
00:05:54.500 --> 00:05:58.963
This is the most detailed
MO we've seen from the Fan.

106
00:06:00.006 --> 00:06:05.719
Does he still strike you
as a "hasn't killed yet" type unsub?

107
00:06:05.720 --> 00:06:07.888
No. he doesn't.

108
00:06:07.889 --> 00:06:09.390
So why didn't he kill Lance?

109
00:06:22.236 --> 00:06:23.863
[nurse] There you go.

110
00:06:24.697 --> 00:06:26.073
Doesn't hurt.

111
00:06:26.824 --> 00:06:28.367
Why doesn't it hurt?

112
00:06:29.827 --> 00:06:35.916
Third degree burns destroy the nerves in
your skin. including your pain receptors.

113
00:06:35.917 --> 00:06:39.252
Lance. anything you can remember
about what happened from the moment

114
00:06:39.253 --> 00:06:42.506
you were abducted will help us catch
the person who did this to you.

115
00:06:45.509 --> 00:06:46.594
I woke up.

116
00:06:47.595 --> 00:06:49.639
I was facing a monitor.

117
00:06:51.182 --> 00:06:52.932
He told me to read off it.

118
00:06:52.933 --> 00:06:54.518
That's all he said.

119
00:06:57.647 --> 00:06:59.190
Is this because of Laura?

120
00:07:00.441 --> 00:07:01.983
What do you mean?

121
00:07:01.984 --> 00:07:05.321
First time you questioned me was because...

122
00:07:06.947 --> 00:07:11.494
because I was being an asshole
to Laura after she dumped me.

123
00:07:13.746 --> 00:07:16.164
Is this all revenge for that?

124
00:07:16.165 --> 00:07:18.541
- It's complicated.
- [Lewis] Mmm.

125
00:07:18.542 --> 00:07:20.669
We think that he may have targeted you

126
00:07:20.670 --> 00:07:25.383
so that we were distracted
investigating you instead of him.

127
00:07:26.008 --> 00:07:27.802
Maybe I was pathetic.

128
00:07:31.222 --> 00:07:32.848
Maybe I still am.

129
00:07:38.104 --> 00:07:40.272
But I don't deserve this.

130
00:07:40.940 --> 00:07:42.274
No. you don't.

131
00:07:43.901 --> 00:07:45.653
So. anything you can remember...

132
00:07:47.571 --> 00:07:49.115
- you contact me.
- [phone buzzes]

133
00:07:49.699 --> 00:07:52.827
And you can show him how not
pathetic you are on the witness stand.

134
00:07:55.246 --> 00:07:56.247
All right?

135
00:07:58.624 --> 00:08:00.166
[Alvez] We got another case.

136
00:08:00.167 --> 00:08:02.043
It doesn't stop.

137
00:08:02.044 --> 00:08:04.045
Of course we do. Where's this one?

138
00:08:04.046 --> 00:08:07.298
Right in our backyard. uh.
two women who made their living

139
00:08:07.299 --> 00:08:11.219
showing their wares on the internet
as camgirls have been murdered.

140
00:08:11.220 --> 00:08:13.179
Regina Madsen and Lexie Clery.

141
00:08:13.180 --> 00:08:14.889
Both were super popular streamers.

142
00:08:14.890 --> 00:08:16.599
Did they stream on the same site?

143
00:08:16.600 --> 00:08:17.684
No. different platforms.

144
00:08:17.685 --> 00:08:20.437
Camgirls stream from all over the world.

145
00:08:20.438 --> 00:08:23.648
How did the unsub find two
in the same geographical area?

146
00:08:23.649 --> 00:08:27.318
Well. if either girl made a video that
showed outfacing windows or mentioned

147
00:08:27.319 --> 00:08:30.321
their location even vaguely.
a good tracker would be able to find them.

148
00:08:30.322 --> 00:08:33.658
Uh. like how we found Laura Boyd
using that tree in the background.

149
00:08:33.659 --> 00:08:35.577
- [Lewis] Mmm.
- Is it possible this is the Fan?

150
00:08:35.578 --> 00:08:37.871
He uses Lance to give us
the message he's not pathetic.

151
00:08:37.872 --> 00:08:40.832
and then leaves the dead bodies
of two camgirls to prove it?

152
00:08:40.833 --> 00:08:43.543
Well. don't jump to conclusions yet.
We don't know if it's connected.

153
00:08:43.544 --> 00:08:45.170
- Garcia. continue.
- Correctamundo.

154
00:08:45.171 --> 00:08:50.133
What we do know is that last
week Regina went live

155
00:08:50.134 --> 00:08:53.970
to show her dead body.
and then last night. same deal with Lexie.

156
00:08:53.971 --> 00:08:56.347
Wait. so now i-is this real money?

157
00:08:56.348 --> 00:08:58.600
[Garcia] Mm-hmm. Green American dollars.

158
00:08:58.601 --> 00:09:00.185
They both asphyxiated on it.

159
00:09:00.186 --> 00:09:01.895
That's a hell of a murder weapon.

160
00:09:01.896 --> 00:09:04.105
[Tyler] Based on the width
of the marks on their bodies.

161
00:09:04.106 --> 00:09:07.901
looks like both women were restrained
with leather belts around their torsos.

162
00:09:07.902 --> 00:09:10.070
Easier for the unsub to force-feed them.

163
00:09:10.071 --> 00:09:11.488
Can we source the leather?

164
00:09:11.489 --> 00:09:13.865
We could try if the unsub
hadn't taken the belts with him.

165
00:09:13.866 --> 00:09:17.035
Wait a minute. Lance Kingston
said he was restrained by leather belts

166
00:09:17.036 --> 00:09:18.912
and that the Fan
took them with him as well.

167
00:09:18.913 --> 00:09:21.581
And Lexie was murdered
the same night Lance was branded.

168
00:09:21.582 --> 00:09:23.542
less than ten miles away
from where we found him.

169
00:09:25.753 --> 00:09:28.004
Now let's jump to conclusions.

170
00:09:28.005 --> 00:09:31.174
There's a shared MO
of binding the victims with belts.

171
00:09:31.175 --> 00:09:33.426
You might see that. but
definitely not three times in one week.

172
00:09:33.427 --> 00:09:38.056
Displaying the bodies of the camgirls
on a live stream speaks to a desire

173
00:09:38.057 --> 00:09:41.852
to get out a message.
but it... it's also a type of exhibitionism.

174
00:09:42.394 --> 00:09:48.149
It is similar to the Fan using Garrity's
live podcast to exhibit his power.

175
00:09:48.150 --> 00:09:49.734
Okay. what's the opposing argument?

176
00:09:49.735 --> 00:09:52.570
[blows raspberries] Well.
if both cases are the Fan.

177
00:09:52.571 --> 00:09:54.739
then his MO is all over the place.

178
00:09:54.740 --> 00:09:57.450
And what. the money stuffed
down the throats

179
00:09:57.451 --> 00:10:01.871
could be him making a statement
about the camgirls perceiving greed.

180
00:10:01.872 --> 00:10:04.707
That's very different
from branding "pathetic."

181
00:10:04.708 --> 00:10:08.086
Exactly. So. we have
two murders and one maiming.

182
00:10:08.087 --> 00:10:10.421
Some of the details overlap. some don't.

183
00:10:10.422 --> 00:10:13.299
So. we are going to go
where the evidence takes us.

184
00:10:13.300 --> 00:10:16.302
These are two different perpetrators.

185
00:10:16.303 --> 00:10:17.929
Dave. you and I will work on the Fan.

186
00:10:17.930 --> 00:10:19.597
The rest of you investigate the camgirls.

187
00:10:19.598 --> 00:10:21.891
no matter what happens.
the clock is ticking.

188
00:10:21.892 --> 00:10:23.268
So. we need to move fast.

189
00:10:23.269 --> 00:10:25.855
- Penelope. can you come with me please?
- Yeah.

190
00:10:28.816 --> 00:10:31.734
I know I'm asking the impossible.
but I need you on both cases.

191
00:10:31.735 --> 00:10:33.570
- Can you do that?
- Absolutely.

192
00:10:33.571 --> 00:10:37.115
That means prioritization. triage.
and when necessary.

193
00:10:37.116 --> 00:10:39.117
you call an audible and ask for help.

194
00:10:39.118 --> 00:10:42.120
Uh. hi. I'm Penelope Garcia.
This is what I live for.

195
00:10:42.121 --> 00:10:44.164
I mean. I know that the gaggle of you

196
00:10:44.165 --> 00:10:47.208
is the John. Paul and George
of crime fighting. but I am the Ringo.

197
00:10:47.209 --> 00:10:48.626
You know. his birthday is July 7th.

198
00:10:48.627 --> 00:10:50.670
That means he's a Cancer
and I'm a Cancer rising.

199
00:10:50.671 --> 00:10:54.175
so we're the same person.
and I've got this.

200
00:10:55.718 --> 00:10:58.845
[Lewis] All right. I have the footage
of Lexie and her boyfriend Rocco.

201
00:10:58.846 --> 00:11:00.263
Let's run down the timeline.

202
00:11:00.264 --> 00:11:02.724
Lexie and Rocco had just
finished a performance.

203
00:11:02.725 --> 00:11:05.727
And the show was.
"Hell if the devil was a dominatrix."

204
00:11:05.728 --> 00:11:06.811
Yes.

205
00:11:06.812 --> 00:11:11.816
So. uh. looking at this. they
did the entire stream from right here.

206
00:11:11.817 --> 00:11:12.902
[Lexie] <i>Bad boy.</i>

207
00:11:14.403 --> 00:11:15.404
[moans]

208
00:11:16.405 --> 00:11:18.406
- [Taser crackles]
- [Rocco groans]

209
00:11:18.407 --> 00:11:20.326
[Lexie gasps. exhales]

210
00:11:21.202 --> 00:11:23.245
[both moan]

211
00:11:26.582 --> 00:11:27.750
[Rocco groans]

212
00:11:28.584 --> 00:11:30.252
Lexie gives Rocco a final shock.

213
00:11:30.794 --> 00:11:32.004
[Rocco groaning]

214
00:11:33.047 --> 00:11:35.757
- Ah. Red. Red.
- Uh. [chuckles]

215
00:11:35.758 --> 00:11:38.636
Rocco yells out the safe word
and they stop the performance.

216
00:11:39.303 --> 00:11:40.678
- Oh.
- Here.

217
00:11:40.679 --> 00:11:42.222
[Rocco panting]

218
00:11:42.223 --> 00:11:45.100
- Better?
- Oh. I'm good now.

219
00:11:46.602 --> 00:11:48.061
Lexie and Rocco always made it a point

220
00:11:48.062 --> 00:11:49.854
to show their audience
their aftercare routine.

221
00:11:49.855 --> 00:11:52.232
<i>Our next show starts in an hour.</i>

222
00:11:52.233 --> 00:11:56.277
Get in the room early and you might
just get a special shout-out from me.

223
00:11:56.278 --> 00:11:57.362
[blows kiss]

224
00:11:57.363 --> 00:11:58.780
[Rocco chuckles]

225
00:11:58.781 --> 00:11:59.823
And everything's fine.

226
00:12:00.866 --> 00:12:04.036
Uh. then Rocco leaves the apartment
at ten o'clock to get them both some food.

227
00:12:04.912 --> 00:12:06.955
- See you later.
- I'll see you in a bit. beautiful.

228
00:12:06.956 --> 00:12:08.414
[Lexie sighs]

229
00:12:08.415 --> 00:12:11.335
GPS on his phone has
him back here by 10:42.

230
00:12:12.169 --> 00:12:13.462
All right. let's go.

231
00:12:19.551 --> 00:12:20.635
All right.

232
00:12:20.636 --> 00:12:23.680
This unsub must have been
stalking Lexie online and off.

233
00:12:23.681 --> 00:12:27.016
He knew when her next show was. but he
also knew to wait until she was alone.

234
00:12:27.017 --> 00:12:30.603
Right. so the unsub watches Rocco leave.
sneaks in here.

235
00:12:30.604 --> 00:12:32.648
Lexie must have thought it was Rocco.

236
00:12:36.277 --> 00:12:37.861
Forget your wallet again?

237
00:12:38.487 --> 00:12:39.946
What?

238
00:12:39.947 --> 00:12:42.366
[screams] Get off of me!

239
00:12:43.033 --> 00:12:44.368
[choking]

240
00:12:49.748 --> 00:12:50.958
He restrains her.

241
00:12:53.711 --> 00:12:56.588
[coughing. panting]

242
00:12:58.382 --> 00:13:00.133
What are you doing?

243
00:13:00.134 --> 00:13:02.510
What do you want? No!

244
00:13:02.511 --> 00:13:04.679
[Tyler] <i>And then he forces
