when you insulted the Fan.

626
00:32:19.500 --> 00:32:21.418
You're right. I did.

627
00:32:21.419 --> 00:32:23.044
I tried to control the story.

628
00:32:23.045 --> 00:32:24.796
I tried to control
what people thought of me.

629
00:32:24.797 --> 00:32:27.842
but I only made things worse
because it's not my story anymore.

630
00:32:28.885 --> 00:32:29.886
It's yours.

631
00:32:33.014 --> 00:32:34.182
Can I tell you what I think?

632
00:32:35.349 --> 00:32:36.350
Please.

633
00:32:38.227 --> 00:32:42.689
I think you see me
as an easily manipulatable patsy.

634
00:32:42.690 --> 00:32:46.943
someone you can get to do
your bidding with a little ego boost

635
00:32:46.944 --> 00:32:48.862
or if that doesn't work.
you throw in a little.

636
00:32:48.863 --> 00:32:52.867
"Oh. Brian. we're not so different.
you and I." Am I close?

637
00:32:57.371 --> 00:32:59.123
Well. let me tell you something.

638
00:32:59.832 --> 00:33:02.710
And this is coming from a very real place.

639
00:33:07.256 --> 00:33:10.384
You and I are very different.

640
00:33:12.303 --> 00:33:13.304
Mmm.

641
00:33:14.972 --> 00:33:17.808
Well. do you even know
what that difference is?

642
00:33:21.020 --> 00:33:23.772
There is
a burgeoning serial killer out there

643
00:33:23.773 --> 00:33:25.774
who I'm pretty sure
has already killed once

644
00:33:25.775 --> 00:33:27.943
but is in a bit of a cooling off period.

645
00:33:27.944 --> 00:33:29.320
And why do you think that is?

646
00:33:30.613 --> 00:33:33.950
What has happened to distract
him to stop him from escalating?

647
00:33:35.409 --> 00:33:36.660
My show.

648
00:33:36.661 --> 00:33:39.372
And that is
the difference between you and me.

649
00:33:40.623 --> 00:33:42.415
I can't stop him from in here.

650
00:33:42.416 --> 00:33:45.127
The BAU can't stop him from anywhere but...

651
00:33:47.421 --> 00:33:48.965
you can.

652
00:33:55.388 --> 00:33:57.348
Thank you for coming to see me.

653
00:34:24.709 --> 00:34:26.626
Wow. What's all this?

654
00:34:26.627 --> 00:34:30.047
Uh. Garcia got all the online chats
Percy had with paying customers.

655
00:34:32.383 --> 00:34:34.802
[chuckles] "Until the room stinks."

656
00:34:37.346 --> 00:34:40.098
I don't know why I'm reading it out loud.
I'm sorry.

657
00:34:40.099 --> 00:34:45.145
Yes. uh... [huffs] ...so way more than half
of these are much older gentlemen.

658
00:34:45.146 --> 00:34:48.648
Yeah. it looks like Percy was
real popular with the AARP army.

659
00:34:48.649 --> 00:34:50.984
Okay. so could our unsub be an older man?

660
00:34:50.985 --> 00:34:54.154
That would explain why
1976 means so much to him.

661
00:34:54.155 --> 00:34:56.239
That could be when his lovemap was formed.

662
00:34:56.240 --> 00:34:57.407
[Lewis] Well. that tracks.

663
00:34:57.408 --> 00:34:59.827
All of our victims
made videos in a '70s persona.

664
00:35:00.453 --> 00:35:02.746
These chats all mentioned food.

665
00:35:02.747 --> 00:35:06.166
So. I looked through some of Regina's
older videos from the time of the chats.

666
00:35:06.167 --> 00:35:09.836
She did a series of mukbangs
with some very regional foods.

667
00:35:09.837 --> 00:35:11.421
What's a mukbang?

668
00:35:11.422 --> 00:35:15.842
Oh. It is when someone eats
an insane amount of food on camera.

669
00:35:15.843 --> 00:35:17.927
I cannot tell you why.
but they are incredibly popular.

670
00:35:17.928 --> 00:35:20.680
[Tyler] So popular
that Lexie did one as well.

671
00:35:20.681 --> 00:35:22.349
Regina had a ton of blue crabs.

672
00:35:22.350 --> 00:35:25.685
Lexie finished hers
with a big box of Berger cookies.

673
00:35:25.686 --> 00:35:27.855
Yeah. we're talking incredibly regional.

674
00:35:28.606 --> 00:35:31.941
Without saying where they lived. these
women still ended up exposing themselves.

675
00:35:31.942 --> 00:35:33.485
- Yeah.
- [Alvez] Mmm.

676
00:35:33.486 --> 00:35:35.445
Solves your geo-profile problem.

677
00:35:35.446 --> 00:35:38.448
Yeah. it's part
of his parasocial delusion.

678
00:35:38.449 --> 00:35:40.992
He wants to believe
these women were his peers.

679
00:35:40.993 --> 00:35:43.870
They grew up in the old neighborhood.
Remember how good it was.

680
00:35:43.871 --> 00:35:46.374
And then when
the relationship soured. he killed them.

681
00:35:47.792 --> 00:35:50.669
We need to comb all of
our victims' communications.

682
00:35:50.670 --> 00:35:53.296
I mean. any mention of regional food
could be our unsub.

683
00:35:53.297 --> 00:35:56.549
Okay. we are gonna have to come back
and help you read through these.

684
00:35:56.550 --> 00:35:59.345
We gotta get to the ME.
They finished Percy's autopsy.

685
00:36:00.096 --> 00:36:01.681
- Sorry.
- [Lewis] Mmm.

686
00:36:02.723 --> 00:36:04.058
Oh. come on.

687
00:36:06.060 --> 00:36:08.728
He put coins inside Percy?

688
00:36:08.729 --> 00:36:12.440
Not only did he use coins this time.
his total was changed.

689
00:36:12.441 --> 00:36:14.693
I took all the cash from Percy's
mouth and stomach.

690
00:36:14.694 --> 00:36:17.320
and then I found two dimes
deep in his bowels.

691
00:36:17.321 --> 00:36:20.658
bringing the grand total to $395.20.

692
00:36:21.492 --> 00:36:27.789
Wait. that's... that's exactly
